<h2 id="模板2：图表中【没有数据变化】"><a href="#模板2：图表中【没有数据变化】" class="headerlink" title="模板2：图表中【没有数据变化】"></a>模板2：图表中【没有数据变化】</h2><h3 id="情况①：一个最大值和一个最小值进行比较，假设要比较的是主题1和主题2的数据，"><a href="#情况①：一个最大值和一个最小值进行比较，假设要比较的是主题1和主题2的数据，" class="headerlink" title="情况①：一个最大值和一个最小值进行比较，假设要比较的是主题1和主题2的数据，"></a>情况①：一个最大值和一个最小值进行比较，假设要比较的是主题1和主题2的数据，</h3><p>其中，主题1的比例最大，主题2的比例最小<br>Given is a … that clearly reveals the remarkable difference between&#x2F;among the statistics<br>of … The【number&#x2F;percentage】of (主题1), (主题2), and (主题3) stands at (数字1&#x2F;比例1), (数字<br>2&#x2F;比例2), and (数字3&#x2F;比例3) respectively. Among all the categories, (主题1) occupies the<br>highest proportion, while the lowest percentage is (主题2).<br>If you look hard enough, you will find that【 】. Two reasons can bear this out. The leading<br>cause is【 】，and it can account for【 】. Secondly, when it comes to【 】, it is well known<br>that【 】. And it can boil down to【 】. Without doubt【 】will exert a far-reaching&#x2F;<br>undesirable&#x2F;unimaginable&#x2F;disastrous effect on【 】.<br>Judging by what is discussed above, it is not difficult to draw the conclusion that【 】.<br>What is to be done? Pretty much everyone agrees on the prescription that【 】.</p>
<h3 id="情况②：一个最大值-x2F-最小值和其他某个数据进行比较，假设要比较的是主题1和主题"><a href="#情况②：一个最大值-x2F-最小值和其他某个数据进行比较，假设要比较的是主题1和主题" class="headerlink" title="情况②：一个最大值&#x2F;最小值和其他某个数据进行比较，假设要比较的是主题1和主题"></a>情况②：一个最大值&#x2F;最小值和其他某个数据进行比较，假设要比较的是主题1和主题</h3><p>2的数据，其中，主题1的比例最大&#x2F;最小，主题2的比例居中<br>Given is a … that clearly reveals the remarkable difference between&#x2F;among the statistics<br>of … The【number&#x2F;percentage】of (主题1), (主题2), and (主题3) stands at (数字1&#x2F;比例1), (数字<br>2&#x2F;比例2), and (数字3&#x2F;比例3) respectively. It can be seen that there is a huge gap between the<br>percentage of (主题1) and (主题2).<br>If you look hard enough, you will find that【 】. Two reasons can bear this out. The leading<br>cause is【 】，and it can account for【 】. Secondly, when it comes to【 】, it is well known<br>that【 】. And it can boil down to【 】. Without doubt【 】will exert a far-reaching&#x2F;<br>undesirable&#x2F;unimaginable&#x2F;disastrous effect on【 】.<br>Judging by what is discussed above, it is not difficult to draw the conclusion that【 】.<br>What is to be done? Pretty much everyone agrees on the prescription that【 】.</p>
<h3 id="情况③：一个最大值-x2F-最小值和其他所有数据一起进行比较，假设主题1的比例最大-x2F"><a href="#情况③：一个最大值-x2F-最小值和其他所有数据一起进行比较，假设主题1的比例最大-x2F" class="headerlink" title="情况③：一个最大值&#x2F;最小值和其他所有数据一起进行比较，假设主题1的比例最大&#x2F;"></a>情况③：一个最大值&#x2F;最小值和其他所有数据一起进行比较，假设主题1的比例最大&#x2F;</h3><p>最小<br>Given is a … that clearly reveals the remarkable difference between&#x2F;among the statistics<br>of … The【number&#x2F;percentage】of (主题1), (主题2), and (主题3) stands at (数字1&#x2F;比例1), (数字<br>2&#x2F;比例2), and (数字3&#x2F;比例3) respectively. It can be seen that there is a huge gap between the<br>percentage of (主题1) and the other categories.<br>If you look hard enough, you will find that【 】. Two reasons can bear this out. The leading<br>cause is【 】，and it can account for【 】. Secondly, when it comes to【 】, it is well known<br>that【 】. And it can boil down to【 】. Without doubt【 】will exert a far-reaching&#x2F;<br>undesirable&#x2F;unimaginable&#x2F;disastrous effect on【 】.<br>Judging by what is discussed above, it is not difficult to draw the conclusion that【 】.<br>What is to be done? Pretty much everyone agrees on the prescription that【 】.</p>
<h1 id="图画作文"><a href="#图画作文" class="headerlink" title="图画作文"></a>图画作文</h1><p>在课程中还介绍了很多其他句型，⽽此处仅提供了⼀种句型组合。如果你对课程内容掌握很扎实，可以按照自⼰的理解来使用其他不同的句型组合。如果你感觉时间很紧，可以直接使用下面这个句型组合。别担⼼，句型之间没有⾼下之分。</p>
<h2 id="模板1：两幅图"><a href="#模板1：两幅图" class="headerlink" title="模板1：两幅图"></a>模板1：两幅图</h2><p>情况①：有文字说明<br>In the first&#x2F;left picture,【主角】,【伴随状语】, is&#x2F;are doing…. By contrast&#x2F;Meanwhile, in<br>the other picture, 【主角】is&#x2F;are doing…. And the drawings are captioned:【文字说明】.<br>If you look hard enough, you will find that【 】. Two reasons can bear this out. The leading<br>cause is【 】，and it can account for【 】. Secondly, when it comes to【 】, it is well known<br>that【 】. And it can boil down to【 】. Without doubt【 】will exert a far-reaching&#x2F;<br>undesirable&#x2F;unimaginable&#x2F;disastrous effect on【 】.<br>Judging by what is discussed above, it is not difficult to draw the conclusion that【 】.<br>What is to be done? Pretty much everyone agrees on the prescription that【 】.<br>情况②：无文字说明<br>In the first&#x2F;left picture,【主角】,【伴随状语】, is&#x2F;are doing…. By contrast&#x2F;Meanwhile, in<br>the other picture, 【主角】is&#x2F;are doing…. Unquestionably, the drawings serve as a reminder<br>of..【图画主题】.<br>If you look hard enough, you will find that【 】. Two reasons can bear this out. The leading<br>cause is【 】，and it can account for【 】. Secondly, when it comes to【 】, it is well known<br>that【 】. And it can boil down to【 】. Without doubt【 】will exert a far-reaching&#x2F;<br>undesirable&#x2F;unimaginable&#x2F;disastrous effect on【 】.<br>Judging by what is discussed above, it is not difficult to draw the conclusion that【 】.<br>What is to be done? Pretty much everyone agrees on the prescription that【 】.</p>
<h2 id="模板2：类似于两幅图的一幅图"><a href="#模板2：类似于两幅图的一幅图" class="headerlink" title="模板2：类似于两幅图的一幅图"></a>模板2：类似于两幅图的一幅图</h2><p>情况①：有文字说明<br>On the left&#x2F;right of the picture,【主角】,【伴随状语】, is&#x2F;are doing….By contrast&#x2F;<br>Meanwhile, on the left&#x2F;right, 【主角】is&#x2F;are doing…. And the drawing is captioned:【文字说<br>明】.<br>If you look hard enough, you will find that【 】. Two reasons can bear this out. The leading<br>cause is【 】，and it can account for【 】. Secondly, when it comes to【 】, it is well known<br>that【 】. And it can boil down to【 】. Without doubt【 】will exert a far-reaching&#x2F;<br>undesirable&#x2F;unimaginable&#x2F;disastrous effect on【 】.<br>Judging by what is discussed above, it is not difficult to draw the conclusion that【 】.<br>What is to be done? Pretty much everyone agrees on the prescription that【 】.<br>情况②：无文字说明<br>On the left&#x2F;right of the picture,【主角】,【伴随状语】, is&#x2F;are doing….By contrast&#x2F;<br>Meanwhile, on the left&#x2F;right, 【主角】is&#x2F;are doing…. Unquestionably, the drawing serves as a<br>reminder of..【图画主题】.<br>If you look hard enough, you will find that【 】. Two reasons can bear this out. The leading<br>cause is【 】，and it can account for【 】. Secondly, when it comes to【 】, it is well known<br>that【 】. And it can boil down to【 】. Without doubt【 】will exert a far-reaching&#x2F;<br>undesirable&#x2F;unimaginable&#x2F;disastrous effect on【 】.<br>Judging by what is discussed above, it is not difficult to draw the conclusion that【 】.<br>What is to be done? Pretty much everyone agrees on the prescription that【 】.</p>
<h2 id="模板3：一幅图"><a href="#模板3：一幅图" class="headerlink" title="模板3：一幅图"></a>模板3：一幅图</h2><p>情况①：有文字说明<br>【主角】in the picture,【伴随状语】，is&#x2F;are doing…. Meanwhile，there is&#x2F;are…. And the<br>drawing is captioned:【文字说明】.<br>If you look hard enough, you will find that【 】. Two reasons can bear this out. The leading<br>cause is【 】，and it can account for【 】. Secondly, when it comes to【 】, it is well known<br>that【 】. And it can boil down to【 】. Without doubt【 】will exert a far-reaching&#x2F;<br>undesirable&#x2F;unimaginable&#x2F;disastrous effect on【 】.<br>Judging by what is discussed above, it is not difficult to draw the conclusion that【 】.<br>What is to be done? Pretty much everyone agrees on the prescription that【 】.<br>情况②：无文字说明<br>【主角】in the picture,【伴随状语】，is&#x2F;are doing…. Meanwhile，there is&#x2F;are….<br>Unquestionably, the drawing serves as a reminder of【图画主题】.<br>If you look hard enough, you will find that【 】. Two reasons can bear this out. The leading<br>cause is【 】，and it can account for【 】. Secondly, when it comes to【 】, it is well known<br>that【 】. And it can boil down to【 】. Without doubt【 】will exert a far-reaching&#x2F;<br>undesirable&#x2F;unimaginable&#x2F;disastrous effect on【 】.<br>Judging by what is discussed above, it is not difficult to draw the conclusion that【 】.<br>What is to be done? Pretty much everyone agrees on the prescription that【 】.</p>
<h1 id="说明"><a href="#说明" class="headerlink" title="说明"></a>说明</h1><ol>
<li>模板的二三段，去年经过实战考验，今年将继续延用，请放心使用。</li>
<li>模板的第一段，分了多种情况，如果理不清楚，请快速回顾一下课程。</li>
<li>最后附上了去年的押题材料，押题没有时效性，所以不要因为是去年提供的押题材料就放松，不管你背什么其他押题，我们给的这份押题材料中的话题，都希望你可以掌握。</li>
<li>⼩作⽂部分不⽤额外准备押题，只需要将第<code>16、17、18</code>炼的笔记中的⼀些⽤词认真复习，且完成整篇专训中的⼩作⽂即可。因为从往年的经验来看，各⼤机构所给的押题材料，最后所谓的押中其实都是类型碰到，⽽不是题⽬押中。⽐如，某机构给出的押题材料中有⼀封道歉信，但具体题⽬可能是李明因为借书问题⽽向李红道歉，⽽考试可能考的是李明因为迟到⽽向⽼师道歉，在这种情况下，各⼤机构依旧会说是押中了题。押中了什么呢？道歉信。但实际上，内容细节截然不同。因此，⼩作⽂部分不建议你做具体题⽬细节层⾯的押题，⽽是将第<code>16、17、18</code>炼的笔记中的⼀些⽤词认真复习（⽐如<code>说点实的</code>、<code>说点虚的</code>），且完成整篇专训中的⼩作⽂即可。</li>
<li>祝你上岸。</li>
</ol>
<h1 id="练习第一段"><a href="#练习第一段" class="headerlink" title="练习第一段"></a>练习第一段</h1><h2 id="1"><a href="#1" class="headerlink" title="1"></a>1</h2><p>题目所给的是一个饼状图，它清楚地揭示了某高校学生对时间观念的显著差异。<br>一定会遵守时间、偶尔会迟到、经常迟到以及没有注意过迟到问题的学生比例分别为 63%，22.6%，7.8%，和6.6%。</p>
<p>Given is a pie chart that clearly reveals the remarkable difference among students’ concepts of time in a certain university.<br>The percentage of students who are punctual, occasionally late, often late and never pay attention to the problem of being late stands at 63%, 22.6%, 7.8%, and 6.6% respectively.</p>
<h2 id="2"><a href="#2" class="headerlink" title="2"></a>2</h2><p>给出的是一个折线图，它清楚地揭示了国内参加体育锻炼人数和体育市场规模的显著变化情况。<br>2011年至2020年间，參加体育锻炼的人数从3.7亿增长到4.35亿。与此同时，体育市场的市场规模也呈现出不断上升的超势，从0.6万亿增长到了1.5万亿。</p>
<p>Given is a line chart that clearly reveals the remarkable change in the number of domestic physical exercise participants and the size of the sports market in China.<br>The number of people taking part in physical exercise climbed from 0.37 billion to 0.435 billion between 2011 and 2020.<br>Meanwhile, there was also an upward&#x2F;downward tendency in the size of the sports market from 600 billion to 1500 billion.</p>
<h2 id="3"><a href="#3" class="headerlink" title="3"></a>3</h2><p>给出的是一个柱状图，它清楚地揭示了某个国家超前消费总额以及人数的显著变化情况。<br>2014年至2020年间，该国超前消费总额从15.37万亿增长到49.57万亿。与此同时，进行超前消费的人数也呈现出不断上升的趋势，从0.38亿增长到了2.3亿。</p>
<p>Given is a bar chart that clearly reveals the remarkable change in total excessive consumption and the number of people who spend money in advance in a certain country.<br>The total excessive consumption climbed from 15.37 trillion to 49.57 trillion between 2014 and 2020.<br>Meanwhile, there was also an upward tendency in the number of people spending money in advance from 38 million to 0.23 billion.</p>
<h2 id="4"><a href="#4" class="headerlink" title="4"></a>4</h2><p>给出的是一个折线图，它清楚地揭示了中国直播电商行业从业人数以及市场规模的显著变化情况。2011年至 2020年间，这个行业的市场规模从0.0366万亿增长到了1.995万亿。<br>与此同时，该行业的从业人员数量也呈现出不断上升的超势，从256万人增长到了1032万人。</p>
<p>Given is a line chart that clearly reveals the remarkable change in the statistics of practitioners and market size in China’s livestreaming e-commerce industry.<br>The amount of market size in this industry climbed from 36.6 billion to 1.995 trillion between 2017 and 2021.<br>Meanwhile, there was also an upward tendency in the number of people who work in this industry from 2.56 million to 10.32 million.</p>
<h1 id="练习第二段"><a href="#练习第二段" class="headerlink" title="练习第二段"></a>练习第二段</h1><h2 id="1-1"><a href="#1-1" class="headerlink" title="1"></a>1</h2><p>如果你观察的⾜够仔细，会发现健康饮⻝对我们的⼈⽣有深远影响。<br>两点原因可以解释。<br>⾸要原因是它可以让我们有更好的精⼒，⽽这能解释为什么精英⼈群更重视健康饮⻝。<br>其次，当提及健康饮⻝时，众所周知的是我们应该减少脂肪和糖类的摄⼊。<br>⽽这可以归结于那些由不健康的饮⻝⽅式导致的肥胖问题。<br>毫⽆疑问，这将对个⼈健康产⽣不利的影响。<br>根据以上所讨论的来判断，不难得出结论：我们应该重视健康饮⻝。应该怎么办呢？<br>很多⼈都赞成这⼀⽅案：我们应当控制每顿饭的分量，不能暴饮暴⻝，多吃⽔果蔬菜以及⻥类。</p>
<p>If you look hard enough, you will find that a healthy diet <code>has a</code> profound impact on our lives.<br>The leading cause is that <code>such a diet</code> can make us have a better energy, and it can account for why the elite attach more importance to healthy eating.<br>Secondly, when it comes to healthy eating, it is well known that we should reduce the intake <code>of</code> fats and sugars.<br>And it can boil down to obesity caused by unhealthy diet<code>s</code>.<br>Without doubt, this will exert <code>an adverse effect</code> on <code>personal</code> <code>health</code>.<br>Judging by what <code>is</code> discusse<code>d</code> above, it is not difficult to draw the conclusion that we should lay <code>emphasis</code> <code>on</code> healthy eating.<br>What is to be done? Pretty much everyone agrees <code>on the prescription</code> that we should control <code>the amount of</code> each <code>meal</code> and do not eat and drink too much.</p>
<h2 id="2-1"><a href="#2-1" class="headerlink" title="2"></a>2</h2><p>如果你观察的⾜够仔细，会发现终身学习对我们的⼯作和⽣活有深远影响。<br>两点原因可以解释。<br>⾸要原因是未来的职业竞争将越来越激烈，⽽这能解释为什么只有持续学习的⼈才有更好的职业发展前景。<br>其次，当提及终身学习时，众所周知的是只有坚持终身学习的⼈才能在未来战胜⼀个⼜⼀个全新的挑战。<br>⽽这可以归结于快速更新的知识。毫⽆疑问，这将对⼈们的学习观念产⽣积极的影 响。<br>根据以上所讨论的来判断，不难得出结论：我们应该重视终身学习。<br>应该怎么办呢？<br>很多⼈都赞成这⼀⽅案：我们需要在各⼤媒体上加⼤对终身学习益处的宣传。</p>
<h2 id="3-1"><a href="#3-1" class="headerlink" title="3"></a>3</h2><p>如果你观察的⾜够仔细，会发现交通拥堵对我们的⽇常⽣活有深远影响。<br>两点原因可以解释。<br>⾸要原因是随着⽣活⽔平的上升越来越多⼈买得起私家⻋，⽽这能解释为什么路上的⻋越来越多。<br>其次，当提及交通拥堵时，众所周知的是公共交通不够便利也是个重要的影响因素。<br>⽽这可以归结于城市的经济和管理⽔平。 毫⽆疑问，这将对城市交通产⽣不利的影响。<br>根据以上所讨论的来判断，不难得出结论：我们应该想办法缓解交通拥堵。<br>应该怎么办呢？ 很多⼈都赞成这⼀⽅案：我们应该⼤⼒发展智能交通，提⾼城市的交通管理⽔平。</p>
<h2 id="4-1"><a href="#4-1" class="headerlink" title="4"></a>4</h2><p>如果你观察的⾜够仔细，会发现⽬标对我们的成功有深远影响。<br>两点原因可以解释。<br>⾸要原因是⽬标可以给我们动⼒，⽽这能解释为什么有⽬标感的⼈更容易实现⽬标。<br>其次，当提及⽬标时，众所周知的是它可以帮助我们度过困难。⽽这可以归结于⽬标带给⼈的⾃信和雄⼼。<br>毫⽆疑问，⽬标将对每个⼈的⼈⽣产⽣积极的影响。<br>根据以上所讨论的来判断，不难得出结论：我们应该拥有明确的⽬标。<br>应该怎么办呢？<br>很多⼈都赞成这⼀⽅案：关键在于把⽬标具体化。</p>
